  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Samuel May, Jr., writes that Mr. Marsh, who is connected with the Bee, is now in Boston. He discusses the problem of C.K. Whipple&apos;s reluctance to go to New York and take over the National Anti-Slavery Standard. Samuel May feels that Whipple is &quot;not equal to the work alone.&quot; William Lloyd Garrison says that &quot;he could not do the Standard work, with only his present experience. There is much talk of your becoming the Editor-in-Chief.&quot;</subfield>
